bptree

Class BPTree<Key extends Comparable<Key>>

  • Object
    • BPTree<Key>
  • Type Parameters:
    Key - the type of the keys stored in this B+ tree. This type has to implement the Comparable interface.

    public class BPTree<Key extends Comparable<Key>>
extends Object
    A generic implementation of a B+ tree that is supposed to support bulk loading. It uses the BPNode class to stored the keys and children.
    See Also:
    BPNode

      • buildLeafLevel

        private List<BPNode<Key>> buildLeafLevel(List<Key> keys)
        Builds a valid leaf level of this B+ tree with the minimal number of leaf nodes for the specified list of keys. This method returns a sorted list of the leaf nodes created in the process (sorted with respect to the keys in the nodes). The children in a leaf node are supposed to be null.
        Parameters:
        keys - a sorted list of keys that are bulk loaded into the B+ tree
        Returns:
        a sorted list of all leaf nodes created in the process, or null if there are no keys to load

      • buildInnerLevel

        private List<BPNode<Key>> buildInnerLevel(List<BPNode<Key>> children)
        Builds a valid inner level of this B+ tree with the minimal number of inner nodes for the specified list of child nodes. This method returns a sorted list of the inner nodes created in the process (sorted with respect to the keys in the nodes). The children in an inner node are supposed to point to the respective child nodes.
        Parameters:
        children - a sorted list of child nodes for which the next inner level is built
        Returns:
        a sorted list of all inner nodes created in the process, or null if there are no children to connect

      • smallestKey

        private Key smallestKey(BPNode<Key> node)
        Retrieves the smallest key in the specified branch of this B+ tree, i.e., the leftmost key of the leftmost branch with respect to the specified node.
        Parameters:
        node - the node that represents the subroot of the branch for which the smallest key should be found
        Returns:
        the smallest key of the branch that has node as (sub)root
